<Author>Muirpik
<Content>Prinz turns out to be a frog my wife and I searched this hotels website and it looke lovely. On arrival we were given a small pokey rom with a smell of drains right next to a main railwy junction. I was awakened by trains at four am and a train went over the points every two minuites after that. We complained and were moved to a smaller room above the bins. The shower room was about five feet by five with an even more smelly drain in the floor. there was one lamp on the wall above the bed suggesting it was realy a single room. It was quieter but nothing like the rooms on the hotels own website.I brought this to the hotel manager who said that these rooms did exist! He did offer a second move but I thought three moves with no guarantee of improvement was a waste of time. We liked Berlin but I would be wary of the star rating system. This four star room would not be acceptable in a half decent bed and breakfast in my opinion. I had paid in full at the time of booking in May which is the only reason we stayed. So beware of this too. 
