<Author>Densley
<Content>Had a lovely stay Have just spent four nights at the Kronprinz and really enjoyed it. Would echo much of what has already been said, although a little out of Berlin it is served by several u and S Bahn lines including the S41 and S42 which are circle lines covering a hugh area of Berlin, travel from the hotel is extremly easy making its quite location no problem and something of an asseet.On arrive at the hotel we were greated by name, all staff were very friendly and what was nice was we saw the same faces over all of our stay. Most staff had good levels of English, perhaps a problem as we really wanted our eldest daughter to practice her German!!!The hotel was extremely clean and comfortable, it is furnished in an older style so may not be to the liking of some travellers, this reflects the age of the building having been built in the 19th Century. Our room did not have A/C but would note that the area is quite so windows can be opened.One note of caution which has not been whooly made clear in previous posts, the hotel only serves breakfast - which was very pleasant, and no other meals. There are many eating places locally and eating out is not that expensive in Berlin. Also if you enjoy sitting in hotel bars, especially at weekends, this hotel may not be the one for you as its bar is only open on weekdays, although drinks can be purchased via the night staff.Please read the hotels website, it reflects accurately what the hotel has to offer.We had a lovely stay in Berlin, it is truly an interesting city and one well worth visiting, our stay was enhanced by a pleasant hotel. If we were to return to Berlin we would happily stay in this hotel again.If you would like to contact me for further details my email address is christaylor@blueyonder.co.uk.Chris TaylorBristol England 
